# An artificial neuron - perceptron

## a perceptron takes several binary inputs and produces a single binary output

    x1,x2,x3 -- w1,w2,w3 -- Pb --> output

    - x represents an input
    - w represents a weight associated with each input
    - P is the perceptron
    - b is a bias unique to the neuron

## the output will be 1 if higher than a threshold and 0 if lower

    output = x1 * w1 + bias
    output = 0 if output < threshold or 1 if output => threshold

    output = 0 if x1 * w1 + bias < threshold or
             1 if x1 * w1 + bias => threshold

 
